<item>
            <title>[HTTPCLIENT-452] DateUtil.formatDate() uses default timezone instead of GMT</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HTTPCLIENT-452</link>
                <project id="12310360" key="HTTPCLIENT">HttpComponents HttpClient</project>
                        <description>DateUtil.formatDate() uses default timezone instead of GMT.  In section 3.3.1,&lt;br/&gt;
RFC 2616 states:  &amp;quot;All HTTP date/time stamps MUST be represented in Greenwich&lt;br/&gt;
Mean Time (GMT), without exception.&amp;quot;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
To reproduce, run the following snippet:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;public static void main(String[] args) {&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;TimeZone tz = TimeZone.getTimeZone(&amp;quot;GMT&amp;quot;);&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;GregorianCalendar gc = new GregorianCalendar(tz);&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;gc.set(1900 + 104, GregorianCalendar.JANUARY, 1, 0, 0, 0);&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;System.out.println(DateUtil.formatDate(gc.getTime()));&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;}&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Expected result:&lt;br/&gt;
Thu, 01 Jan 2004 00:00:00 GMT&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Actual result (if your default timezone is PST):&lt;br/&gt;
Wed, 31 Dec 2003 16:00:00 PST</description>
                <environment>Operating System: All&lt;br/&gt;
Platform: All</environment>
